attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.text: Discard all Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This is an extremely rare Pikachu card. You're very lucky to have found it!

name: Surskit

attacks.name: Sweet Scent
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

name: Masquerain

abilities.name: Tool Reversal
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may put a Pokémon Tool card attached to 1 of your Pokémon into your hand.

flavorText: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.

name: Lileep
rules: Put this card onto your Bench only with the effect of Root Fossil Lileep

abilities.name: Prehistoric Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokémon on the bottom of your deck.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

name: Cradily

attacks.name: Lifesplosion
attacks.text: For each Energy attached to this Pokémon, search your deck for a Stage 2 Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

name: Tropius

attacks.name: Return
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Energy Press
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.

name: Karrablast
flavorText: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

name: Shelmet

attacks.name: Yawn
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.

name: Accelgor

attacks.name: Retribution
attacks.text: If an Escavalier you had in play was Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, put all Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon into your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Signal Beam
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: When its body dries out, it weakens. So it wraps a membrane around itself for protection while it spits poison.

name: Virizion-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Verdant Wind
abilities.text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Grass Energy attached to it can't be affected by any Special Conditions. (Remove any Special Conditions affecting those Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Emerald Slash
attacks.text: You may search your deck for 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Genesect

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for 2 Grass Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Jet Impact
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: Genesect-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Red Signal
abilities.text: When you attach a Plasma Energy from your hand to this Pokémon, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with his or her Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Megalo Cannon
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness or Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Larvesta

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.

name: Volcarona

attacks.name: Solar Transporter
attacks.text: Reveal the top 5 cards of your deck and put all Team Plasma cards you find there into your hand. Discard the other cards.

attacks.name: Leech Life
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Thought to be an embodiment of the sun, it appeared during a bitterly cold winter and saved Pokémon from freezing.

name: Squirtle

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It shelters itself in its shell then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

name: Wartortle

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

name: Blastoise

abilities.name: Deluge
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

name: Lapras

attacks.name: Cleanse Away
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.

name: Remoraid

attacks.name: Bubble Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

name: Octillery

attacks.name: Sharpshooting
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Bubble Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

name: Suicune

abilities.name: Safeguard
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by Pokémon-EX.

flavorText: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

name: Snorunt

attacks.name: Powder Snow
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.

name: Glalie

attacks.name: Powder Snow
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Reflect Energy
attacks.text: Move a Water Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

name: Froslass

abilities.name: Cursed Glare
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't attach any Special Energy cards from his or her hand to his or her Pokémon.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degrees F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

name: Relicanth

attacks.name: Fossil Hunt
attacks.text: Put 2 Item cards that have Fossil in their names from your discard pile into your hand.

flavorText: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

name: Snover
flavorText: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.

name: Abomasnow

attacks.name: Bang Heads
attacks.text: Both this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon are now Confused.

flavorText: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.

name: Tirtouga
rules: Put this card onto your Bench only with the effect of Cover Fossil

abilities.name: Prehistoric Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokémon on the bottom of your deck.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. It swam skillfully and dove to depths beyond half a mile.

name: Carracosta

attacks.name: Fossil Clutch
attacks.text: You may discard an Item card that has Fossil in its name from your hand. If you do, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.

name: Ducklett

attacks.name: Splatter
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: Kyurem-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Giga Frost
attacks.text: Discard 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

name: Eelektrik

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.

name: Eelektross

attacks.name: Crush and Burn
attacks.text: Discard as many Energy attached to your Pokémon as you like. This attack does 30 damage times the number of Energy cards you discarded.

attacks.name: Thunder Tempest
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.

name: Drifloon

attacks.name: Creepy Wind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Wind Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: These Pokémon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.

name: Drifblim

abilities.name: Drifting Balloon
abilities.text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Team Plasma Pokémon in play.

attacks.name: Derail
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can't be a fixed destination.

name: Uxie

attacks.name: Psypower
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: When Uxie flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.

name: Mesprit

abilities.name: Mental Shroud
abilities.text: If you have Uxie and Azelf in play, each of your Pokémon has no Weakness.

flavorText: When Mesprit flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.

name: Azelf

attacks.name: Trading Places
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psyjamming
attacks.text: Move as many Special Energy attached to your opponent's Pokémon to your opponent's other Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: When Azelf flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.

name: Munna

attacks.name: Focused Wish
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.

name: Musharna

attacks.name: Precognitive Dream
attacks.text: Draw 3 cards. This Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

name: Sigilyph

abilities.name: Toolbox
abilities.text: This Pokémon may have up to 4 Pokémon Tool cards attached to it. (If this Pokémon loses this Ability, discard Pokémon Tool cards attached to this Pokémon until only 1 Pokémon Tool card remains.)

flavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

name: Solosis

attacks.name: Hide
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.

name: Duosion

attacks.name: Focused Wish
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

name: Reuniclus

attacks.name: Barrier Attack
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Telekinesis of Nobility
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders psychically.

name: Golett
flavorText: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

name: Golurk

attacks.name: Iron Fist of Justice
attacks.text: If you have any Team Plasma Pokémon in play, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Shadow Punch
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

flavorText: Golurk were created to protect people and Pokémon. They run on a mysterious energy.

name: Machop
flavorText: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.

name: Machoke

attacks.name: Last-Chance Chop
attacks.text: If this Pokémon's remaining HP is 10, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.

name: Machamp

abilities.name: Badge of Discipline
abilities.text: The damage of each of your Fighting Pokémon's attacks isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Close Combat
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is increased by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.

name: Machamp

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Reinforced Lariat
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.

name: Throh

attacks.name: Freestyle Strike
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Shoulder Throw
attacks.text: Does 80 damage minus 20 damage for each Colorless in the Defending Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

flavorText: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

name: Sawk

attacks.name: Kick of Righteousness
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Team Plasma Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.

name: Archen
rules: Put this card onto your Bench only with the effect of Plume Fossil

abilities.name: Prehistoric Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokémon on the bottom of your deck.

flavorText: It was revived from an ancient fossil. Not able to fly, it lived in treetops and hopped from one branch to another.

name: Archeops

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Swift Dive
attacks.text: If this Pokémon's remaining HP is 50 or less, this attack's base damage is 50.

flavorText: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.

name: Houndour

attacks.name: Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Dark Clamp
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Blazing Claws
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Team Plasma Pokémon, this attack does 60 more damage, and the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

name: Aron

attacks.name: Iron Head
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: In order to build up its steel body, it eats iron ore. This pesky Pokémon is known to eat railroad tracks.

name: Lairon

attacks.name: Iron Head
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Lairon fight over territory, and when their steel bodies collide, sparks fly.

name: Aggron

attacks.name: Knock Back
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Aura of the Land
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don't take it lightly.

name: Jirachi-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Stellar Guidance
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Hypnostrike
attacks.text: Both this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon are now Asleep.

name: Escavalier

attacks.name: Steamroll
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Slashing Strike
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

flavorText: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

name: Bagon
flavorText: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

name: Shelgon

attacks.name: Knock Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.

name: Salamence

abilities.name: Breakwing
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may discard all Pokémon Tool cards attached to each of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Gaia Crush
attacks.text: Discard any Stadium card in play.

flavorText: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.

name: Dialga-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Reverse Edge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, put a card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Fast Forward
attacks.text: For each Plasma Energy attached to this Pokémon, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Palkia-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Strafe
attacks.text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dimension Heal
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon 20 damage for each Plasma Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Axew

attacks.name: Strong Bond
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Supporter card named Iris, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: Its large tusks have a tendency to break, but each time they grow back, they grow in harder and sturdier.

name: Fraxure

attacks.name: Paralyzing Gaze
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

name: Haxorus

attacks.name: Dragonaxe
attacks.text: Does 40 damage times the amount of Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Strike of the Champion
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Team Plasma Pokémon, it is Knocked Out. (If the Defending Pokémon is not a Team Plasma Pokémon, this attack does nothing.)

flavorText: Its tusks are incredibly destructive. They can easily slice through a thick, sturdy steel column every time.

name: Druddigon

attacks.name: Big Swing
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It runs through the narrow tunnels formed by Excadrill and Onix. It uses its sharp claws to catch prey.

name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby play only when it feels safe.

name: Porygon
flavorText: A man-made Pokémon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.

name: Porygon2

attacks.name: Destructive Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Plasma Transfer
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Plasma Energy attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tri Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.

name: Teddiursa

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

name: Ursaring

attacks.name: Adrenalash
attacks.text: During your next turn, each of this Pokémon's attacks does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

name: Chatot

attacks.name: Misinformation
attacks.text: Discard all Pokémon Tool cards attached to each of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tone-Deaf
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Its tongue is just like a human's. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.

You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

When the Team Plasma Pokémon this card is attached to is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).
You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).
You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

attacks.text: This attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness or Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

rules: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).
You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).
You can't have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Propagation
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put this Pokémon into your hand.

flavorText: This extremely rare Pokémon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.

attacks.name: Leaf Wallop
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Leaf Wallop does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: This extremely rare Pokémon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.

name: Dusknoir

abilities.name: Sinister Hand
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon to another of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Shadow Punch
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Rare Candy
rules: Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 2 card in your hand that evolves from that Pokémon, put that card on the Basic Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.) You can't use this card during your first turn or on a Basic Pokémon that was put into play this turn.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Tangela

attacks.name: Flog
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Flog
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it's fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.

name: Shuckle

attacks.name: Share
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Stab
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

name: Cherubi

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.

name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Ambush Bite
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage and discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Using its tentacles to lash itself to trees, it lies in wait for prey, luring it close with sweet-smelling drool.

name: Snivy

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

name: Servine

attacks.name: Wring Out
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

name: Serperior

abilities.name: Royal Heal
abilities.text: At any time between turns, heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Leaf Tornado
attacks.text: Move as many Grass Energy attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.

name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: Leaf Boomerang
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: Sewaddle
flavorText: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

name: Swadloon

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny

abilities.name: Leaf Tailor
abilities.text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached to it has no Weakness.

attacks.name: Cutting Arm
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

name: Crustle

attacks.name: Hard Press
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.

name: Virizion

attacks.name: Double Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Leaf Wallop
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Leaf Wallop does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

name: Genesect

attacks.name: Gaia Blaster
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: Charmander

attacks.name: Draw In
attacks.text: Attach 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

name: Charmeleon

attacks.name: Raging Claws
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

flavorText: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

name: Charizard

attacks.name: Split Bomb
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Scorching Fire
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

name: Vulpix

attacks.name: Firebreathing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

name: Ninetales

attacks.name: Color Coordination
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any basic Energy attached to it that is the same type as the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: Each of its nine tails is imbued with supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.

name: Moltres

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

name: Victini

abilities.name: Victory Star
abilities.text: Once during your turn, after you flip any coins for an attack, you may ignore all effects of those coin flips and being flipping those coins again. You can't use more than 1 Victory Star Ability each turn.

attacks.name: Stored Power
attacks.text: Move all Energy attached to this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Victini-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Turbo Energize
attacks.text: Search your deck for 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Intensifying Burn
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Pokémon-EX, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Tepig

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It can deftly dodge its foe's attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: Pignite

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When it trouble, it emits smoke.

name: Emboar

abilities.name: Inferno Fandango
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: Reshiram

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 or more for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Blue Flare
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

name: Reshiram-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Glinting Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Brave Fire
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 50 damage to itself.

name: Magikarp

attacks.name: Flailing Flop
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.

name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Howling Rampage
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the number of Prize cards both players have taken.

flavorText: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

name: Articuno

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Water Splash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

name: Prinplup

attacks.name: Water Splash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.

name: Empoleon

attacks.name: Emperor's Strike
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has fewer remaining HP than the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.

name: Phione

attacks.name: Pull Out
attacks.text: Put a card from your discard pile on top of your deck.

attacks.name: Aqua Boomerang
attacks.text: Return this Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

flavorText: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

name: Oshawott

attacks.name: Razor Shell
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.

name: Dewott

attacks.name: Aqua Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 10 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.

name: Samurott

abilities.name: Shell Armor
abilities.text: Any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.

name: Tympole
flavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad

attacks.name: Round
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

flavorText: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

name: Seismitoad

attacks.name: Round
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

flavorText: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

name: Kyurem

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Glaciate
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: Kyurem-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Frozen Wings
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hail Blizzard
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Hail Blizzard during your next turn.

name: Keldeo-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Rush In
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch this Pokémon with your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Secret Sword
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Zapdos

attacks.name: Random Spark
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Thundering Hurricane
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

name: Plusle

attacks.name: Tag Draw
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 4 cards. If Minun is on your Bench, draw 4 more cards.

attacks.name: Positive Ion
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

name: Minun

attacks.name: Negative Ion
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 30 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Electrishower
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

name: Emolga

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.

name: Thundurus

attacks.name: Charge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Disaster Volt
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

name: Zekrom

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Bolt Strike
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.

name: Zekrom-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Glinting Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Strong Volt
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Psyslash
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: X Ball
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psydrive
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Natu
flavorText: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

name: Xatu

attacks.name: Fortunate Draw
attacks.text: You and your opponent play Rock-Paper-Scissors. The player who wins draws 3 cards. The player who loses discards the top 3 cards of his or her deck.

attacks.name: Miracle Wing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.

name: Misdreavus
flavorText: A Pokémon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

name: Mismagius

attacks.name: Absorb Life
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

name: Ralts

attacks.name: Mind Bend
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Mind Bend
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

name: Sableye

attacks.name: Tight Jaw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

name: Croagunk

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

name: Toxicroak

attacks.name: Revenge
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 70 more damage.

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: The croaking that Toxicroak produces before a battle is for churning the poison it has stored in its poison sac.

name: Woobat

attacks.name: Dual Cut
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

name: Swoobat

attacks.name: Energy Gift
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for 2 Psychic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.

name: Sigilyph

abilities.name: Safeguard
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by Pokémon-EX.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

name: Trubbish

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: Garbodor

abilities.name: Garbotoxin
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, each Pokémon in play, in each player's hand, and in each player's discard pile has no Abilities (except for Garbotoxin).

flavorText: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: Gothita

attacks.name: Hypnotic Gaze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothita

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It stares intently at everything. It can become so obsessed with watching that it doesn't notice attacks.

name: Gothorita

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: Gothitelle

abilities.name: Magic Room
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Item cards from his or her hand.

attacks.name: Madkinesis
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: Solosis
flavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others

name: Solosis

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: Reuniclus

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order.

attacks.name: Net Force
attacks.text: Does 40 damage times the number of Reuniclus you have in play.

flavorText: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: Chandelure-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Cursed Drop
attacks.text: Put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Eerie Glow
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Confused.

name: Meloetta

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Echoed Voice
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

name: Riolu

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.

name: Lucario

abilities.name: Reflexive Retaliation
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Aura Sphere
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.

name: Gallade

attacks.name: Nerve Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Pandemonium Blade
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.

flavorText: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

name: Excadrill-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dig Out
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your deck. If that card is a basic Energy card, attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Break Ground
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Stunfisk

attacks.name: Muddy Water
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon).

attacks.name: Rumble
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

name: Terrakion

attacks.name: Retaliate
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

name: Landorus

attacks.name: Abundant Harvest
attacks.text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Gaia Hammer
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."

name: Meloetta

attacks.name: Magical Dance
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Shooting Star Pirouette
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

name: Spiritomb

abilities.name: Sealing Scream
abilities.text: Each player can't play any ACE SPEC cards from his or her hand.

attacks.name: Hexed Mirror
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a number of cards equal to the number of cards in your opponent's hand.

flavorText: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

name: Darkrai-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Dark Cloak
abilities.text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Darkness Energy attached to it has no Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Night Spear
attacks.text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Zorua

attacks.name: Ascension
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon. (This counts as evolving this Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: Zoroark

attacks.name: Brutal Bash
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the number of Darkness Pokémon you have in play.

attacks.name: Dark Rush
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokémon.

flavorText: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: Cobalion

attacks.name: Energy Press
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Iron Breaker
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

name: Altaria

attacks.name: Cleave
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, discard all Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.

name: Rayquaza

attacks.name: Dragon Pulse
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

name: Gible
flavorText: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

name: Gabite

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

name: Garchomp

attacks.name: Mach Cut
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragonblade
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

flavorText: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

name: Deino

attacks.name: Deep Growl
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Power Breath
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

name: Zweilous

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

name: Hydreigon

abilities.name: Dark Trance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Darkness Energy attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragonblast
attacks.text: Discard 2 Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

name: Black Kyurem-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dragon Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Freeze Shock
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

name: White Kyurem-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dragon Stream
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Ice Burn
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon. The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Lugia-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Overflow
abilities.text: If your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack of this Pokémon, take 1 more Prize card.

attacks.name: Plasma Gale
attacks.text: Discard a Plasma Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you can't discard a Plasma Energy, this attack does nothing.

name: Swablu

attacks.name: Glare and Peck
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: For some reason, it likes to land on people's heads softly and act like it's a hat.

name: Minccino

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

name: Cinccino

abilities.name: Smooth Coat
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Echoed Voice
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

name: Druddigon

abilities.name: Rough Skin
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Clutch
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.

name: Bouffalant

attacks.name: Revenge
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 70 more damage.

attacks.name: Head Charge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

name: Tornadus

attacks.name: Energy Wheel
attacks.text: Move an Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hurricane
attacks.text: Move a basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: Bianca
rules: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Cedric Juniper
rules: Put a Pokémon from your hand face down in front of you and tell your opponent its name. Your opponent guesses the height of that Pokémon. Reveal that Pokémon. If your opponent guessed right, he or she draws 3 cards. If your opponent guessed wrong, you draw 3 cards. Return the Pokémon to your hand. (You can't choose a Pokémon that doesn't have the height printed on the card.)
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Crushing Hammer
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Energy Switch
rules: Move a basic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Double Colorless Energy
rules: Double Colorless Energy provides ColorlessColorless Energy.

name: Reshiram

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Blue Flare
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

name: Zekrom

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Bolt Strike
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.

name: Snivy

attacks.name: Growth
attacks.text: Attach a Grass Energy from your hand to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: Servine

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

name: Serperior

abilities.name: Royal Garden
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Grass Energy attached to it, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

flavorText: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior's noble eyes.

name: Growlithe

attacks.name: Rest
attacks.text: Heal all damage from this Pokémon. This Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.

name: Torchic
flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Charm
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.

name: Ralts

attacks.name: Hypnotic Gaze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Tiptoe Step
attacks.text: Draw a card for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

name: Gardevoir

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Eternal Radiance
attacks.text: Move all damage counters from this Pokémon to the Defending Pokémon. This Pokémon can't use Eternal Radiance during your next turn.

flavorText: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

name: Meloetta-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Brilliant Voice
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Round
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

name: Stunfisk

attacks.name: Attract
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

flavorText: When its opponent can't be paralyzed, it contorts itself with unexpected speed and flops away.

name: Purrloin

attacks.name: Captivate
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

name: Teddiursa

attacks.name: Honey Snack
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

name: Ursaring

attacks.name: Picnic Weather
attacks.text: Put a Teddiursa from your discard pile onto your Bench. Then, attach an Energy card from your discard pile to that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

name: Audino

attacks.name: Relaxed Roll
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number heads.

flavorText: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.

name: Minccino

attacks.name: Tail Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.

name: Cinccino

abilities.name: Smooth Coat
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Echoed Voice
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

name: Elesa
rules: Search your deck for 3 Pokémon Tool cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Shaymin-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Synthesis
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Revenge Blast
attacks.text: Does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Reshiram

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Blue Flare
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

name: Emolga

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It glides on its outstretched membrane while shocking foes with the electricity stored in the pouches on its cheeks.

name: Mew-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Versatile
abilities.text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of any Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's). (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

attacks.name: Replace
attacks.text: Move as many Energy attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Meloetta-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Brilliant Voice
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Round
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

name: Pansage

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

name: Simisage

attacks.name: Fire's Power
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Fire Energy attached to it, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: Sewaddle
flavorText: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

name: Swadloon

attacks.name: Double Razor Leaf
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

name: Swadloon

attacks.name: Grass Cocooning
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny

attacks.name: Nurturing
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your Pokémon. Search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: Leavanny

attacks.name: Triple Cutter
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

name: Cottonee

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.

name: Cottonee

attacks.name: Cotton Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Helping Hand
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Cotton Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Encore
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can only use that attack.

attacks.name: U-turn
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

name: Petilil

attacks.name: Stun Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

name: Lilligant

attacks.name: Bemusing Aroma
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

name: Deerling

attacks.name: Wild Kick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

name: Sawsbuck

attacks.name: Push Down
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

name: Virizion

attacks.name: Giga Drain
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sacred Sword
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Sacred Sword during your next turn.

flavorText: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

name: Pansear

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600º F.

name: Simisear

attacks.name: Water's Power
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Water Energy attached to it, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

name: Darumaka
flavorText: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

name: Darmanitan

attacks.name: Rock Smash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Fire Punch
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Its internal fire burns at 2,500º F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

name: Panpour

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

name: Simipour

attacks.name: Grass' Power
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Grass Energy attached to it, heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rushing Water
attacks.text: Move an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Basculin

attacks.name: Flail
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Final Gambit
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are tails, this Pokémon does 80 damage to itself.

flavorText: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they'll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

name: Basculin

attacks.name: Splatter
attacks.text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's school.

name: Ducklett

attacks.name: Roost
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon. This Pokémon can't retreat during your next turn.

flavorText: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

name: Swanna

attacks.name: Wing Dance
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Air Slash
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.

name: Cubchoo

attacks.name: Powder Snow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Rest
attacks.text: Heal 60 damage from this Pokémon. This Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

name: Cubchoo
flavorText: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.

name: Beartic

attacks.name: Sheer Cold
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Icicle Crash
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

flavorText: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: Beartic

attacks.name: Icy Wind
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Superpower
attacks.text: You may do 20 more damage. If you do, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

name: Emolga

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membranes and released while it is gliding.

name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

name: Galvantula

attacks.name: Stun Needle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: Thundurus

attacks.name: Charge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Disaster Volt
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

name: Woobat

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

name: Swoobat

attacks.name: Phat Sound
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

name: Venipede

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.

name: Whirlipede

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 60 more damage.

attacks.name: Steamroller
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

flavorText: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

name: Scolipede

attacks.name: Toxic Claws
