attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.

attacks.name: Wild Horn
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

name: Sigilyph

attacks.name: Reflect
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Telekinesis
attacks.text: Does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

name: Sigilyph

attacks.name: Quick Turn
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Psychic Assault
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

name: Gothita

attacks.name: Hypnotic Gaze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothita
flavorText: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

name: Gothorita

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: Gothorita

attacks.name: Deleting Glare
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

name: Gothitelle

abilities.name: Magic Room
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Item cards from his or her hand.

attacks.name: Madkinesis
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: Gothitelle

attacks.name: Mental Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If tails, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

name: Roggenrola

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokémon if that damage is 40 or less.

flavorText: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

name: Roggenrola

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

name: Boldore

attacks.name: Smack Down
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has Fighting Resistance, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

name: Boldore

attacks.name: Hard Crash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If tails, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.

name: Gigalith

attacks.name: Shear
attacks.text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are Fighting Energy cards, attach them to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rock Bullet
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Fighting Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The solar energy absorbed by its body's orange crystals is magnified internally and fired from its mouth.

name: Drilbur

attacks.name: Hone Claws
attacks.text: During your next turn, each of this Pokémon's attacks does 30 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

name: Excadrill

attacks.name: Drill Run
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

name: Excadrill

attacks.name: Dig
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

name: Throh

attacks.name: Scarf Hold
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

name: Sawk

attacks.name: Five Fierce Chops
attacks.text: Flip 5 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

flavorText: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

name: Sandile
flavorText: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

name: Krokorok

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

name: Krookodile

abilities.name: Black Eyes
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Thrash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If tails, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

name: Terrakion

attacks.name: Sacred Sword
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Sacred Sword during your next turn.

flavorText: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

name: Purrloin

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

flavorText: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

name: Liepard

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Claw Rend
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

name: Zorua

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: Zoroark

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: Vullaby

attacks.name: Rear Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.

name: Mandibuzz

attacks.name: Bone Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Dark Pulse
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

flavorText: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

name: Ferroseed

attacks.name: Pin Missile
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: Ferrothorn

attacks.name: Steel Feelers
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Gyro Ball
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Then, your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

name: Ferrothorn

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Power Whip
attacks.text: Does 10 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: Klink

attacks.name: Gear Grind
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.

name: Klang

attacks.name: Metal Sound
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don't return.

name: Klinklang

attacks.name: Charge Beam
attacks.text: Attach an Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Zap Cannon
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon can't use Zap Cannon during your next turn.

flavorText: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: Cobalion

attacks.name: Metal Horns
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sacred Sword
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Sacred Sword during your next turn.

flavorText: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

name: Patrat

attacks.name: Hyper Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.

name: Watchog

attacks.name: Watcheck
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck and put them back on top of his or her deck in any order.

attacks.name: Quick Tail Smash
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: Pidove
flavorText: Each follows its Trainer's orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

name: Tranquill

attacks.name: Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.

name: Unfezant

attacks.name: Tailwind
attacks.text: Attach an Energy from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Feather Strike
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage. If tails, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves fell close to anyone other than their Trainers.

name: Audino

attacks.name: Powerful Slap
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Heal Pulse
attacks.text: Heal 50 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radar-like ability to understand its surrounding through slight sounds.

name: Minccino

attacks.name: Last Resort
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

name: Cinccino

attacks.name: Captivate
attacks.text: Switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fluffy Tail
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.

name: Rufflet
flavorText: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

name: Rufflet

attacks.name: Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: Braviary

attacks.name: Brave Bird
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky get from their peers.

name: Tornadus

attacks.name: Energy Wheel
attacks.text: Move an Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hurricane
attacks.text: Move a basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: Bianca
rules: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Cheren
rules: Draw 3 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Crushing Hammer
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Great Ball
rules: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. You may reveal a Pokémon you find there and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Max Potion
rules: Heal all damage from 1 of your Pokémon. Then, discard all Energy attached to that Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Pokémon Catcher
rules: Switch your opponent's Active Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Recycle
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, put a card from your discard pile on top of your deck.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Thundurus

attacks.name: Charge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Disaster Volt
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

name: Tornadus

attacks.name: Energy Wheel
attacks.text: Move an Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hurricane
attacks.text: Move a basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: Sewaddle

attacks.name: Leaf Boomerang
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: Swadloon

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny

abilities.name: Leaf Tailor
abilities.text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached to it has no Weakness.

attacks.name: Cutting Arm
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: Petilil

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

name: Lilligant

attacks.name: Aromax
attacks.text: Heal all damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Windmill
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.

name: Dwebble

attacks.name: Withdraw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: The Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

name: Crustle

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: Karrablast

attacks.name: Mysterious Evolution
attacks.text: If Shelmet is in play, search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon. (This counts as evolving this Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: When they feel threatened, they spit acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokémon targets Shelmet.

name: Foongus
flavorText: For some reason, this Pokémon resembles a Poké Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

name: Amoonguss

attacks.name: Toxic
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

name: Shelmet

attacks.name: Mysterious Evolution
attacks.text: If Karrablast is in play, search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon. (This counts as evolving this Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

name: Accelgor

attacks.name: Acid Spray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Slashing Strike
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

flavorText: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.

name: Virizion

attacks.name: Double Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Leaf Wallop
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Leaf Wallop attack does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

name: Victini

abilities.name: Victory Star
abilities.text: Once during your turn, after you flip any coins for an attack, you may ignore all effects of those coin flips and being flipping those coins again. You can't use more than 1 Victory Star Ability each turn.

attacks.name: Stored Power
attacks.text: Move all Energy attached to this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Victini

attacks.name: V-create
attacks.text: If you have 4 or fewer Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Pansear

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600° F.

name: Simisear

attacks.name: Double Fire
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

name: Heatmor

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Incinerate
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard a Pokémon Tool card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.

name: Larvesta

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

name: Larvesta

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

name: Volcarona

attacks.name: Fiery Dance
attacks.text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Heat Wave
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.

name: Tympole
flavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad

attacks.name: Round
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

flavorText: It lives in water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

name: Seismitoad

attacks.name: Round
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

flavorText: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

name: Tirtouga
rules: Put this card onto your Bench only with the effect of Cover Fossil
flavorText: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: Carracosta

abilities.name: Solid Rock
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, reduce that damage by 50 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: Vanillite

attacks.name: Icicle Barb
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

name: Vanillish

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice particles and hiding among them.

name: Vanilluxe

attacks.name: Double Freeze
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. If either of them is heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.

name: Frillish
flavorText: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: Jellicent

abilities.name: Cursed Body
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: The fate of ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitats: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: Cryogonal

attacks.name: Icy Wind
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Ice Shard
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Fighting Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.

name: Cryogonal

attacks.name: Ice Chain
attacks.text: Switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Frost Vanish
attacks.text: You may return this Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

flavorText: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.

name: Kyurem

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Glaciate
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It generates powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: Blitzle

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: Zebstrika

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Shock Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard all Lightning Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Emolga

attacks.name: Electrichain
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage if you have any Lightning Pokémon on your Bench.

flavorText: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.

name: Tynamo

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik

abilities.name: Dynamotor
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: Eelektross

attacks.name: Acid
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Wild Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: Stunfisk

attacks.name: Thunder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

name: Victini

attacks.name: V-blast
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It creates an unlimited supply of energy inside its body, which it shares with those who touch it.

name: Yamask

attacks.name: Perplex
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

name: Yamask

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

name: Cofagrigus

attacks.name: Damagriiigus
attacks.text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Perplex
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

name: Cofagrigus

abilities.name: Durable Body
abilities.text: If this Pokémon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokémon is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP becomes 10 instead.

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.

name: Trubbish

attacks.name: Garbage Collection
attacks.text: Put a card from your discard pile on top of your deck.

flavorText: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.

name: Garbodor

attacks.name: Gentle Wrap
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Gunk Shot
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.

name: Solosis
flavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: Reuniclus

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order.

attacks.name: Net Force
attacks.text: Does 40 damage times the number of Reuniclus you have in play.

flavorText: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: Reuniclus

attacks.name: Dizzy Punch
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Mind Bend
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

name: Elgyem

attacks.name: Calm Mind
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon had never been seen until it appeared from far in the desert 50 years ago.

name: Elgyem

attacks.name: First Contact
attacks.text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent's brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: Beheeyem

attacks.name: Synchronoise
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that shares a type with the Defending Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.

name: Litwick

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel it burns.

name: Litwick

attacks.name: Teleportation Burst
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leaches off the life force of any who follow it.

name: Lampent

attacks.name: Luring Light
attacks.text: Switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: Chandelure

abilities.name: Cursed Shadow
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Eerie Glow
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Confused.

flavorText: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Gigalith

attacks.name: Core Cannon
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Fighting Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

name: Timburr

attacks.name: Pummel
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

flavorText: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr

attacks.name: Pummel
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: Conkeldurr

abilities.name: Craftsmanship
abilities.text: This Pokémon gets +20 HP for each Fighting Energy attached to it.

attacks.name: Top Down
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

flavorText: It it thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

name: Conkeldurr

attacks.name: Chip Away
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Swing Around
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

name: Archen
rules: Put this card onto your Bench only with the effect of Plume Fossil

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: Archeops

abilities.name: Ancient Power
abilities.text: Each play can't play any Pokémon from his or her hand to evolve his or her Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rock Slide
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: Stunfisk

attacks.name: Trickle
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a volt of electricity.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attack. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: Mienshao

attacks.name: Feint
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

flavorText: It wield the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arms attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

name: Golett

attacks.name: Dynamic Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

name: Golurk

attacks.name: Hammer Arm
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Hurricane Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.

name: Terrakion

attacks.name: Retaliate
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

name: Landorus

attacks.name: Abundant Harvest
attacks.text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Gaia Hammer
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."

name: Pawniard

attacks.name: Iron Head
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.

name: Bisharp

attacks.name: Finishing Blow
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 50 more damage.

attacks.name: Night Slash
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

name: Deino
flavorText: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

name: Zweilous

attacks.name: Double Hit
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.

name: Hydreigon

abilities.name: Dark Aura
abilities.text: All Energy attached to this Pokémon are Darkness Energy instead of their usual type.

attacks.name: Berserker Blade
attacks.text: Does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

name: Escavalier

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Twineedle
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Blades comprise this Pokémon's entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

name: Bisharp

attacks.name: Energy Stream
attacks.text: Attach a Metal Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Metal Scissors
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

name: Durant

attacks.name: Devour

name: Vullaby

attacks.name: Whirlwind

attacks.name: Cavalry Lance

flavorText: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

name: Klink

attacks.name: Smash Turn

name: Klinklang

attacks.name: Metal Blast

attacks.name: Lock Gear
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

flavorText: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.

name: Bisharp

attacks.name: Aerial Ace
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

name: Chansey

attacks.name: Sing
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Double-Edge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Chansey

attacks.name: Continuous Tumble
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Blissey

abilities.name: Softboiled

attacks.name: Double-Edge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 60 damage to itself.

flavorText: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Because its genetic makeup is irregular, it quickly changes its form due to a variety of causes.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Because its genetic makeup is irregular, it quickly changes its form due to a variety of causes.

name: Chatot

attacks.name: Tone-Deaf
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Its tongue is just like a human's. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.

name: Lillipup

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.

name: Herdier

attacks.name: Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It has a black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: Stoutland

attacks.name: Special Fang
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has a Special Energy attached to it, this attack does 40 more damage.

attacks.name: Ferocious Bellow
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 30 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: Haxorus

attacks.name: Stunning Uppercut
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

name: Tornadus-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Blow Through
attacks.text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Power Blast
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Cheren
rules: Draw 3 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Dark Claw
rules: Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.
If this card is attached to a Darkness Pokémon, each of the attacks of that Pokémon does 20 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Dark Patch
rules: Attach a basic Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Darkness Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Enhanced Hammer
rules: Discard a Special Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Hooligans Jim & Cas
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 3 random cards from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals those cards and shuffles them into his or her deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: N
rules: Each player shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck. Then, each player draws a card for each of his or her remaining Prize cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Old Amber Aerodactyl
rules: Look at the bottom 7 cards of your deck. You may reveal an Aerodactyl you find there and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Professor Juniper
rules: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

name: Random Receiver
rules: Reveal cards from the top of your deck until you reveal a Supporter card. Put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Rare Candy
rules: Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 2 card in your hand that evolves from that Pokémon, put that card on the Basic Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.) You can't use this card during your first turn or on a Basic Pokémon that was put into play this turn.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Twist Mountain
rules: Once during each player's turn, that player may flip a coin. If heads, that player may play a Restored Pokémon from their hand onto their Bench.
This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.

name: Ultra Ball
rules: Discard 2 cards from your hand. (If you can't discard 2 cards, you can't play this card.) Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: This extremely rare Pokémon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.

name: Archeops

attacks.name: Rock Slide

name: Pokémon Catcher
rules: Switch your opponent's Active Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

name: Hoppip

attacks.name: Flail Around
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

name: Skiploom

attacks.name: Bullet Seed
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

name: Jumpluff

abilities.name: Leave It to the Wind
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may return this Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

attacks.name: Acrobatics
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Blown by the seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

name: Yanma

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It can hover in one spot by flapping its wings at high speed. It flits about to guard its territory.

name: Yanmega

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.

name: Wurmple

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

flavorText: Often targeted by bird Pokémon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.

name: Silcoon

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokémon if that damage is 60 or less.

flavorText: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.

name: Beautifly

attacks.name: Triple Energy
attacks.text: Search your deck for 3 different types of basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Drainpour
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Despite its looks, it is aggressive. It jabs with its long, thin mouth if disturbed while collecting pollen.

name: Cascoon

attacks.name: Tangle Drag
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

name: Nincada

attacks.name: Dig
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

name: Ninjask

abilities.name: Cast-off Shell
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for Shedinja and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Night Slash
attacks.text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

name: Roselia

attacks.name: Double Whip
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Relaxing Fragrance
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage and remove all Special Conditions from this Pokémon.

flavorText: The more healthy the Roselia, the more pleasant its flowers' aroma. Its scent deeply relaxes people.

name: Roselia

attacks.name: Needling Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: The more healthy the Roselia, the more pleasant its flowers' aroma. Its scent deeply relaxes people.

name: Roserade

attacks.name: Crosswise Whip
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Poison Point
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.

name: Roserade

abilities.name: Le Parfum
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for any card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Squeeze
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.

name: Maractus

attacks.name: Stun Needle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Reinforced Needle
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

name: Foongus

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Vulpix

attacks.name: Singe

flavorText: It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.

name: Ninetales

abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with his or her Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hexed Flame

flavorText: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. It can live for a thousand years.

name: Magmar

name: Magmortar

attacks.name: Flame Screen

attacks.name: Flamethrower

name: Ho-Oh-EX

attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each different type of basic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Magikarp

attacks.name: Soggy Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.

name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Swing Around
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Lullaby
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.

name: Wailord

attacks.name: Water Cannon
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Giant Wave
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Giant Wave during your next turn.

flavorText: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

name: Feebas

attacks.name: Add-a-Dash
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, draw a card.

flavorText: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.

name: Milotic

attacks.name: Clear Search
attacks.text: Search your deck for any 3 cards and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Water Pulse

flavorText: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

name: Spheal

attacks.name: Unstoppable Roll

flavorText: It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.

name: Sealeo
flavorText: It habitually spins things on its nose. By doing so, it learns textures and odors.

name: Walrein

attacks.name: Ice Entomb

flavorText: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.

name: Buizel
flavorText: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through the water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

name: Floatzel
flavorText: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and carry off prey.

name: Tympole

attacks.name: Bubble

flavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad

attacks.name: Supersonic
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, the can make wave in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

name: Seismitoad

attacks.name: Echoed Voice
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Drain Punch
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

name: Alomomola

attacks.name: Mysterious Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

name: Mareep

attacks.name: Cotton Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Thunder Jolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

name: Flaaffy

attacks.name: Cotton Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying weakness and resistance).

flavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

name: Ampharos

abilities.name: Electromagnetic Wall
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, whenever your opponent attaches an Energy from his or her hand to 1 of his or her Pokémon, put 3 damage counters on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Electrobullet
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.

name: Electrike

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

name: Electrike

attacks.name: Quick Turn
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

name: Manectric

attacks.name: Energy Crush
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flash Impact
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

name: Manectric

attacks.name: Energy Assist
attacks.text: Attach 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

name: Emolga

attacks.name: Call for Family

flavorText: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.

name: Mew-EX

abilities.name: Versatile
abilities.text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of any Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's). (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

attacks.name: Replace
attacks.text: Move as many Energy attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Dustox

attacks.name: Hazardous Scales
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep, Burned, and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Aerial Ace
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: Toxic powder is scattered with each flap. At night, it is known to strip leaves off trees lining boulevards.

name: Shedinja

abilities.name: Empty Shell
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.

attacks.name: Cursed Drop
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one's spirit.

name: Drifloon

attacks.name: Sneaky Placement

flavorText: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a "Signpost for Wandering Spirits."

name: Drifloon
flavorText: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a "Signpost for Wandering Spirits."

name: Drifblim

attacks.name: Shadow Steal

attacks.name: Plentiful Placement

flavorText: At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.

name: Sigilyph

abilities.name: Safeguard
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by Pokémon-EX.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

name: Trubbish

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: Garbodor

abilities.name: Garbotoxin
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, each Pokémon in play, in each player's hand, and in each player's discard pile has no Abilities (except for Garbotoxin).

flavorText: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: Gothita

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order.

flavorText: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

name: Gothorita

attacks.name: Hypnoblast
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

name: Gothitelle

attacks.name: Doom Decree
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Black Magic
attacks.text: Does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: Golett

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

name: Golurk

attacks.name: Ghost Hammer
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon has no Weakness.

name: Cubone

name: Marowak

attacks.name: Vortex Chop

flavorText: From its birth, this savage Pokémon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

name: Nosepass
flavorText: When endangered, it may protect itself by raising its magnetism and drawing iron objects to its body.

name: Baltoy

attacks.name: Reverse Spin
attacks.text: Your opponent shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck and draws 4 cards.

flavorText: It move by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

name: Claydol

attacks.name: Rapid Spin
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Then, your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rock Smash

flavorText: An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokémon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.

name: Roggenrola

attacks.name: Stone Edge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

name: Boldore

attacks.name: Rock Cannon
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.

name: Gigalith

attacks.name: Revenge Cannon
attacks.text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on each of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: The solar energy absorbed by its body's orange crystals is magnified internally are fired from its mouth.

name: Throh

attacks.name: Squeeze
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Superpower
attacks.text: You may do 20 more damage. If you do, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.

name: Sawk

attacks.name: Defensive Stance
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon. Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Karate Chop
attacks.text: Does 70 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

flavorText: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

name: Stunfisk

attacks.name: Muddy Water
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Rumble
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

name: Terrakion-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Rock Tumble
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Pump-up Smash
attacks.text: Attach 2 basic Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.

name: Honchkrow

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: You may have your opponent switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Diving Swipe
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

flavorText: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called "Summoner of Night."

name: Houndour
flavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Fire Fang
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

name: Stunky

attacks.name: Acid Spray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.

name: Skuntank

attacks.name: Smogscreen
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

flavorText: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

name: Aron

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.

name: Lairon

attacks.name: Wreak Havoc
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

flavorText: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes it steely body against others to fight over territory.

name: Aggron

abilities.name: Toppling Wind
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Giga Horn
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.

name: Registeel-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Triple Laser
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to 3 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Protect Charge
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Probopass

attacks.name: Magnetic Lines
attacks.text: You may move an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Heavy Nose
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

name: Durant

attacks.name: Pull Out
attacks.text: Put a card from your discard pile on top of your deck.

attacks.name: Iron Head
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Durant dig nests in mountains. They build their complicated, interconnected tunnels into mazes.

name: Altaria

abilities.name: Fight Song
abilities.text: Your Dragon Pokémon's attacks do 20 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.

name: Rayquaza-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Celestial Roar
attacks.text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are Energy cards, attach them to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragon Burst
attacks.text: Discard all basic Fire Energy or all basic Lightning Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage times the number of Energy you discarded.

name: Gible
flavorText: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

name: Gible

attacks.name: Sand-Attack
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Knock Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

name: Gabite

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

name: Gabite

abilities.name: Dragon Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Dragon Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

name: Garchomp

attacks.name: Mach Cut
attacks.text: Discard a Special Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragonblade
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

flavorText: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

name: Garchomp

attacks.name: Sand Tomb
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

name: Giratina-EX
rules: Pokémon-EX rule: When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragon Pulse
attacks.text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

name: Deino

attacks.name: Deep Growl
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Power Breath
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It tends to bit everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

name: Deino

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

name: Zweilous

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

name: Zweilous

attacks.name: Draw In
attacks.text: Attach 2 Darkness Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.

name: Hydreigon

abilities.name: Dark Trance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Darkness Energy attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragonblast
attacks.text: Discard 2 Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

name: Hydreigon

attacks.name: Consume
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Destructor Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

name: Aipom

attacks.name: Double Hit
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It lives high among the treetops. It can us its tail as freely and cleverly as its hands.

name: Ambipom

attacks.name: Double Hit
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Hand Fling
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of cards in your hand.

flavorText: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.

name: Slakoth

attacks.name: Smack ‘n' Slack
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It spends nearly all its time in a day sprawled out. Just seeing it makes one drowsy.

name: Vigoroth

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: Its heart beats at a tenfold tempo, so it cannot sit still for even a moment.

name: Slaking

abilities.name: Unobservant
abilities.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, this Pokémon can't attack.

attacks.name: Crushing Blow
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: The world's laziest Pokémon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.

name: Swablu

attacks.name: Sing
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It can't relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes of dirt with its wings.

name: Swablu

name: Bidoof

attacks.name: Bang Heads
attacks.text: Both this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon are now Confused.

flavorText: A comparison revealed that Bidoof's front teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata's.

name: Bibarel

attacks.name: Amnesia

attacks.name: Tumbling Tackle
attacks.text: Both this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon are now Asleep.

name: Audino

attacks.name: Wake-up Beam

attacks.name: Drain Slap

flavorText: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has radarlike ability to understand its surroundings through slight sounds.

name: Minccino

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: They great one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

name: Bouffalant

attacks.name: Gold Breaker
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Pokémon-EX, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a trail.

name: Rufflet

attacks.name: Chirp

attacks.name: Sharp Beak
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: Braviary

attacks.name: Fury Attack

flavorText: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

If the Pokémon this card is attached to is Knocked Out by damage from an attack, put that Pokémon into your hand. (Discard all cards attached to that Pokémon.)
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).
